AD_COLUMN.NAME: Temperature
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Temperature of the agent, value between 0 and 2
AD_COLUMN.HELP:
In the context of a Large Language Model (LLM) that is used by the agent, "temperature" is a parameter that controls the randomness of the model's responses:
Low temperature (e.g., 0.1): Produces more predictable and conservative outputs. High temperature (e.g., 1.0 or higher): Produces more random and creative outputs.
Temperature adjusts the probability distribution for selecting the next word in a sequence, balancing between coherence and creativity.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Check Hosts
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Check the hosting from Etendo to Copilot and back.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: This process check if the ETENDO_HOST is available and if the response is 200. If so, checks the call to COPILOT_HOST verifying the 200 response, and then chek the call to Etendo again but using ETENDO_HOST_DOCKER.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Active
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.
